doi.definition: serial code used to uniquely identify digital objects like academic papers

planet.definition: any planet beyond the Solar System
planet.remark: the catalogue limit is 60 Jupiter mass for a planet

satellite.definition: celestial body that orbits a planet

detection_method.definition: Methods which have detected the exoplanet

disk kinematics.definition: Detection of a Keplerian perturbation due to a planet in a gas disk
Detection of a Keplerian perturbation due to a planet in a gas disk

t_peri.definition: Time of passage at the periapse for eccentric orbits

t_conj.definition: Time of the star-planet upper conjunction when using the RV method

t_0.definition: Time of passage at the center of the transit light curve for the primary transit

t0_sec.definition: Time of passage at the center of the transit light curve for the secondary transit

lambda_ang.definition: sky-projected angle between the planetary orbital spin and the stellar rotational spin (Rossiter-McLaughlin anomaly)

impact_param.definition: Minimum distance of the planet to the stellar center for transiting planets with respect to the stellar radius

tvr.definition: Time of zero increasing radial velocity (i.e. when the planet moves towards the observer) for circular orbits

k.definition: semi-amplitude of the radial velocity curve

mass_meas_method.definition: Method of measurement of the planet mass

theoretical.definition: Mass determination derived from a theoretical model

rad_meas_method.definition: Method of measurement of the planet radius

theoretical.definition: Radius determination derived from a theoretical model

hot_pt.definition: Longitude of the planet hottest point

ag.definition: Geometric Albedo (ratio of reflected radiation to incident radiation)

temp_fig.definition: Link to a figure showing the temperature measurement

molecule_fig.definition: Link to a figure showing the molecule observation

object_status.definition: object status, must be in this list : confirmed, candidate, controversial, retracted

discovered_date.definition: date of discovery of the astonomic object

embargo_end_date.definition: Date on which we can publish the object in the catalog

remarks.definition: Any additional information on the object

url_simbad.definition: url corresponding to the object on simbad

publication_status.definition: status of the reveal's object publication, must be in this list : R — Published in a refereed paper, S — Submitted to a professional journal, C — Announced on a professional conference, W — Announced on a website

gs.definition: Gravitational system, in this part you can fill in all the gravitational relations of the objects described in the file in list with the format described below cf. [Document name] for examples
